# Vercel Deployment Environment Variables

## Required Environment Variables

Add these in your Vercel project settings (Settings > Environment Variables):

### 1. Backend API URL
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend-url.herokuapp.com
# Or use your deployed backend URL (Railway, Render, etc.)
```

### 2. Blockchain Configuration
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_CAMP_TESTNET_RPC=https://rpc.camp.network/testnet
NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID=325000
```

### 3. Smart Contract Addresses (after deployment)
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_IP_REGISTRY_ADDRESS=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_ROYALTY_ENGINE_ADDRESS=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS=0x...
```

### 4. Optional: Analytics & Monitoring
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS=G-XXXXXXXXXX
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://...@sentry.io/...
```

## Deployment Steps

1. Push your code to GitHub
2. Import project to Vercel
3. Configure environment variables
4. Deploy!

See DEPLOYMENT.md for detailed instructions.
